1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:29,980
Thank you for watching!

2
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:33,800
Your pattern is scored based on the number 10.

3
00:00:34,220 --> 00:00:36,380
So out of 10 is your mark.

4
00:00:36,900 --> 00:00:39,860
As you can see, it's split up into two parts.

5
00:00:40,120 --> 00:00:43,200
We have our accuracy and our presentation on this side.

6
00:00:43,260 --> 00:00:45,080
So we'll start off with the accuracy first.

7
00:00:45,640 --> 00:00:50,060
So your accuracy is actually scored from a 4.

8
00:00:50,440 --> 00:00:56,800
So from the number 4, you're actually marked during your presentation of your pattern.

9
00:00:56,920 --> 00:00:59,880
And then with that one, any mistakes that you make,

10
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:04,940
if it's a minor mistake, you get a minus of a 0.1.

11
00:01:05,040 --> 00:01:08,480
If it's a major mistake, you get minus 0.3.

12
00:01:08,860 --> 00:01:12,480
So I'll just let you guys know about the difference between the two.

13
00:01:12,860 --> 00:01:16,860
So with a minor mistake, it's a very, very small thing.

14
00:01:16,940 --> 00:01:19,500
So say we're doing an outer block.

15
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:23,000
If it's not your shoulder height, maybe it's a little bit lower,

16
00:01:23,440 --> 00:01:26,260
or maybe it's a tiny bit higher, that's a minor mistake.

17
00:01:26,360 --> 00:01:27,500
So that's a 0.1.

18
00:01:27,620 --> 00:01:29,400
A major mistake would be,

19
00:01:29,400 --> 00:01:31,680
you're supposed to do an outer block in the pattern,

20
00:01:31,840 --> 00:01:34,860
but you forget and you say you do a reach hand strike instead.

21
00:01:35,220 --> 00:01:36,800
So that would be a major mistake.

22
00:01:37,240 --> 00:01:41,620
So with a minor mistake, let's say pattern 1, for example,

23
00:01:42,040 --> 00:01:43,460
there's 20 steps.

24
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:51,020
It's not uncommon to have up to maybe 14, 15 mistakes in the 20 steps.

25
00:01:51,420 --> 00:01:53,140
So the reason for that would be,

26
00:01:53,780 --> 00:01:57,040
it needs to be absolutely perfect to get,

27
00:01:57,040 --> 00:02:01,280
to not get a deduction of 0.1.

28
00:02:01,640 --> 00:02:06,140
So it's not uncommon to say there's 20 steps and you made,

29
00:02:06,240 --> 00:02:07,660
let's say, 15 mistakes.

30
00:02:08,420 --> 00:02:09,380
So what would that be?

31
00:02:09,720 --> 00:02:12,540
So we'll leave that there on this side,

32
00:02:12,640 --> 00:02:15,520
and we'll come back and we'll just calculate the score at the end.

33
00:02:15,980 --> 00:02:17,780
So a major mistake,

34
00:02:18,480 --> 00:02:20,540
say you're supposed to turn to the left,

35
00:02:20,620 --> 00:02:21,640
but you turn to the right,

36
00:02:21,920 --> 00:02:22,880
that would be a major mistake.

37
00:02:22,880 --> 00:02:26,960
So obviously we do want to try to avoid any of these major mistakes.

38
00:02:27,560 --> 00:02:29,920
So after we've done our pattern,

39
00:02:30,120 --> 00:02:32,540
that's when we move on to the presentation side.

40
00:02:32,640 --> 00:02:34,200
So the presentation, as you can see,

41
00:02:34,500 --> 00:02:35,720
it's from a score of 6.

42
00:02:36,240 --> 00:02:39,480
This 6 is actually split up into 3 parts.

43
00:02:39,840 --> 00:02:41,500
So we have 1, 2, 3 here.

44
00:02:41,940 --> 00:02:43,140
So with this one,

45
00:02:43,920 --> 00:02:46,860
for a score of 2 is your power and speed.

46
00:02:47,280 --> 00:02:49,560
Your rhythm is also a score of 2,

47
00:02:49,560 --> 00:02:53,580
and your expression of energy is also scored out in 2 as well.

48
00:02:53,900 --> 00:02:56,380
So we'll start off with the power and speed.

49
00:02:57,040 --> 00:03:01,640
So with this one, whether it's your blocks, your kicks, your strikes, your punches,

50
00:03:01,640 --> 00:03:03,140
anything you are that you do,

51
00:03:03,140 --> 00:03:04,840
you need to be nice and strong,

52
00:03:04,840 --> 00:03:06,840
and it has to be fast as well.

53
00:03:06,840 --> 00:03:09,840
So it's one thing to have a very strong punch,

54
00:03:09,840 --> 00:03:11,340
or a very fast punch,

55
00:03:11,340 --> 00:03:17,640
but it has to be both strong and fast to get high in that category.

56
00:03:17,640 --> 00:03:19,640
So the next part is your rhythm.

57
00:03:19,640 --> 00:03:22,140
So the rhythm, when you do start your pattern,

58
00:03:22,140 --> 00:03:23,640
there is a rhythm to the pattern.

59
00:03:23,640 --> 00:03:26,040
It's not just really fast all the way through,

60
00:03:26,040 --> 00:03:27,340
it's not slow all the way through.

61
00:03:27,340 --> 00:03:32,140
There's a slow, fast, slow, fast kind of aspect to it as well.

62
00:03:32,140 --> 00:03:34,640
So you do need to kind of work on your rhythm,

63
00:03:34,640 --> 00:03:36,340
and that's also scored out of 2.

64
00:03:37,340 --> 00:03:39,540
The last bit is your expression of energy.

65
00:03:39,540 --> 00:03:42,040
So what is expression of energy?

66
00:03:42,040 --> 00:03:44,740
So that's basically how loud you shout,

67
00:03:44,740 --> 00:03:47,540
so how much intensity you have during your pattern as well.

68
00:03:47,540 --> 00:03:50,940
So say you're doing your pattern really well,

69
00:03:50,940 --> 00:03:52,840
it's really fast and it's strong,

70
00:03:52,840 --> 00:03:54,240
your rhythm is really great,

71
00:03:54,240 --> 00:03:55,640
but you're not shouting very loud,

72
00:03:56,040 --> 00:03:57,440
you can kind of tell,

73
00:03:57,440 --> 00:04:01,040
the judges can kind of tell you're not really confident,

74
00:04:01,040 --> 00:04:02,540
you're a little bit nervous,

75
00:04:02,540 --> 00:04:05,940
so that's what we need to kind of improve on as well.

76
00:04:05,940 --> 00:04:09,040
So I'll just come around to this side.

77
00:04:09,040 --> 00:04:12,540
So with this one, for colour belts and black belts,

78
00:04:12,540 --> 00:04:14,140
it's actually scored a little bit differently.

79
00:04:14,140 --> 00:04:16,040
So if you're a colour belt,

80
00:04:16,040 --> 00:04:18,540
you'll actually, your average,

81
00:04:18,540 --> 00:04:21,240
so where the judges actually mark you from,

82
00:04:21,240 --> 00:04:24,940
it's actually from a 1.1.

83
00:04:24,940 --> 00:04:25,840
So this is your average,

84
00:04:25,840 --> 00:04:29,640
so say you did alright,

85
00:04:29,640 --> 00:04:31,940
you did average compared to everyone else,

86
00:04:31,940 --> 00:04:34,640
your score for 1, 2 and 3,

87
00:04:34,640 --> 00:04:36,140
it'll start from a 1.1.

88
00:04:36,140 --> 00:04:39,840
So if you're less than average in the judges' eyes,

89
00:04:39,840 --> 00:04:41,240
you might go down to,

90
00:04:41,240 --> 00:04:42,640
say for your power and speed,

91
00:04:42,640 --> 00:04:45,740
you might get a 1 or even a 0.9.

92
00:04:45,740 --> 00:04:46,840
If you did really great,

93
00:04:46,840 --> 00:04:49,740
you might even get a 1.3 or a 1.4.

94
00:04:49,740 --> 00:04:53,740
So each individual category,

95
00:04:53,740 --> 00:04:55,840
you need to obviously get as high as you can.

96
00:04:55,840 --> 00:04:57,940
If you're a black belt,

97
00:04:57,940 --> 00:05:00,040
generally, depending on the competition,

98
00:05:00,040 --> 00:05:02,140
you will be scored from a 1.3.

99
00:05:02,140 --> 00:05:05,540
So 1.3 would be your average that you start from.

100
00:05:05,540 --> 00:05:09,940
So say your power and speed was above average,

101
00:05:09,940 --> 00:05:15,540
you might get scored a 1.4 for now.

102
00:05:15,540 --> 00:05:19,840
Say your rhythm was only about average,

103
00:05:19,840 --> 00:05:21,340
it wasn't amazing,

104
00:05:21,340 --> 00:05:23,640
it might be just a 1.3,

105
00:05:23,640 --> 00:05:25,640
but let's say you didn't shout very loud.

106
00:05:25,840 --> 00:05:27,940
So your expression of energy,

107
00:05:27,940 --> 00:05:29,640
your average was 1.3,

108
00:05:29,640 --> 00:05:31,140
it might drop to say,

109
00:05:31,140 --> 00:05:33,340
let's say a 1.0.

110
00:05:33,340 --> 00:05:35,840
So with this one,

111
00:05:35,840 --> 00:05:38,340
we'll come over down to this slide.

112
00:05:38,340 --> 00:05:41,440
So with this one,

113
00:05:41,440 --> 00:05:42,140
as I was saying,

114
00:05:42,140 --> 00:05:45,140
it's a total of 10.

115
00:05:45,140 --> 00:05:46,140
So let's see.

116
00:05:46,140 --> 00:05:47,640
And for presentation,

117
00:05:47,640 --> 00:05:52,840
we had 1.7, 1, 2, 3.

118
00:05:52,840 --> 00:05:55,240
So we had a 3.7.

119
00:05:55,240 --> 00:05:57,540
Let's say you made 15 mistakes.

120
00:05:57,540 --> 00:05:59,040
So with this one, obviously,

121
00:05:59,040 --> 00:06:00,340
don't be too discouraged

122
00:06:00,340 --> 00:06:04,340
if you do get pretty high in your mistakes.

123
00:06:04,340 --> 00:06:06,240
This is with the judges.

124
00:06:06,240 --> 00:06:08,940
We have three judges usually at the panel

125
00:06:08,940 --> 00:06:10,440
and each judge, obviously,

126
00:06:10,440 --> 00:06:11,440
it's very subjective.

127
00:06:11,440 --> 00:06:14,840
So from their point of view,

128
00:06:14,840 --> 00:06:16,140
you might have made a lot of mistakes

129
00:06:16,140 --> 00:06:19,140
or you may have made not a lot of mistakes as well.

130
00:06:19,140 --> 00:06:21,040
So that's why we have the three judges

131
00:06:21,040 --> 00:06:23,740
and we average it out as well.

132
00:06:23,740 --> 00:06:24,740
Okay, so

133
00:06:25,240 --> 00:06:28,540
say we did our 15 mistakes,

134
00:06:28,540 --> 00:06:29,740
very small mistakes.

135
00:06:29,740 --> 00:06:33,640
So if they're all minus 0.1,

136
00:06:33,640 --> 00:06:35,540
it'd be 1.5.

137
00:06:35,540 --> 00:06:39,040
So you go 4.0 minus 1.5,

138
00:06:39,040 --> 00:06:43,240
which equals 2.5.

139
00:06:43,240 --> 00:06:45,740
So this would be your accuracy score.

140
00:06:45,740 --> 00:06:48,140
So with our presentation like before,

141
00:06:48,140 --> 00:06:50,840
we're saying we've got a 3.7 here.

142
00:06:50,840 --> 00:06:53,640
So we add these numbers

143
00:06:53,640 --> 00:06:55,140
after the judges are finished

144
00:06:55,140 --> 00:06:55,840
scoring.

145
00:06:55,840 --> 00:06:57,840
So you would get for this pattern,

146
00:06:57,840 --> 00:07:00,840
a 6.2,

147
00:07:00,840 --> 00:07:02,340
which is actually very good.

148
00:07:02,340 --> 00:07:04,540
So I'll just talk about a little bit more now

149
00:07:04,540 --> 00:07:06,640
about this number here.

150
00:07:06,640 --> 00:07:08,940
So if you're a color belt,

151
00:07:08,940 --> 00:07:11,840
if you're a yellow or above

152
00:07:11,840 --> 00:07:13,340
and you do your patterns,

153
00:07:13,340 --> 00:07:17,640
it's not uncommon generally for a color belt.

154
00:07:17,640 --> 00:07:22,840
The average is about a 4 to 5.

155
00:07:22,840 --> 00:07:24,440
So if you get a number between

156
00:07:25,140 --> 00:07:27,740
4 and 5 out of 10 for your pattern,

157
00:07:27,740 --> 00:07:30,940
that's actually generally considered pretty good.

158
00:07:30,940 --> 00:07:32,740
So anything above that,

159
00:07:32,740 --> 00:07:34,740
you can consider yourself pretty good.

160
00:07:34,740 --> 00:07:35,940
If you're a black belt,

161
00:07:35,940 --> 00:07:37,940
the average would say,

162
00:07:37,940 --> 00:07:40,340
because we're talking here about

163
00:07:40,340 --> 00:07:42,940
the higher presentation as an average,

164
00:07:42,940 --> 00:07:48,340
anything from 5 to 6

165
00:07:48,340 --> 00:07:52,040
is actually considered pretty good.

166
00:07:52,040 --> 00:07:54,840
And anything over a 7,

167
00:07:54,840 --> 00:07:56,840
is actually considered almost world-class.

168
00:07:56,840 --> 00:07:59,840
So if you get a 7 for any of your patterns,

169
00:07:59,840 --> 00:08:02,240
you generally need to pat yourself on the back

170
00:08:02,240 --> 00:08:03,940
because you did an amazing job.

171
00:08:03,940 --> 00:08:07,340
So we just went through our form day scoring.

172
00:08:07,340 --> 00:08:10,940
So just remember accuracy is a 4.0,

173
00:08:10,940 --> 00:08:13,240
presentation is a 6.0,

174
00:08:13,240 --> 00:08:16,640
accuracy is judged during your pattern,

175
00:08:16,640 --> 00:08:18,640
presentation is after,

176
00:08:18,640 --> 00:08:22,440
and then we get the two scores that we add up

177
00:08:22,440 --> 00:08:23,640
and we get that number.

178
00:08:23,640 --> 00:08:24,440
So with this one,

179
00:08:24,440 --> 00:08:28,340
obviously, say I was judge number one,

180
00:08:28,340 --> 00:08:30,440
I would give you a 6.2.

181
00:08:30,440 --> 00:08:32,840
There was another judge on the other side,

182
00:08:32,840 --> 00:08:35,840
maybe he saw a couple more mistakes than I did,

183
00:08:35,840 --> 00:08:37,640
and maybe this one would be a little bit lower,

184
00:08:37,640 --> 00:08:39,440
it might be a 5 point something.

185
00:08:39,440 --> 00:08:41,640
Another judge on the other side,

186
00:08:41,640 --> 00:08:43,440
they scored a little bit higher.

187
00:08:43,440 --> 00:08:45,140
So we get the three numbers

188
00:08:45,140 --> 00:08:47,240
and then we average that as well.

189
00:08:47,240 --> 00:08:49,640
So I hope this helped you guys.

190
00:08:49,640 --> 00:08:52,340
So make sure you enjoy your Punto competitions

191
00:08:52,340 --> 00:08:53,940
and anytime,

192
00:08:53,940 --> 00:08:55,240
and make sure, obviously,

193
00:08:55,240 --> 00:08:57,840
you record down your numbers as well.

194
00:08:57,840 --> 00:09:00,140
So it's very important.

195
00:09:02,140 --> 00:09:04,840
This reading.

196
00:09:17,140 --> 00:09:19,140
Minor errors, major errors.

197
00:09:19,140 --> 00:09:20,140
So real time,

198
00:09:20,140 --> 00:09:21,540
we cannot pause the video this time,

199
